  "prompt": "What are the top ten PC games ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"top ten\" PC games ever is subjective and can vary based on criteria such as sales, impact, innovation, and player preference. However, many games consistently appear on various lists due to their popularity and influence. Here's a list of ten iconic PC games that are often regarded as some of the best:\n\n1. **Half-Life 2 (2004)** - A groundbreaking first-person shooter known for its storytelling, physics, and gameplay mechanics.\n\n2. **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt (2015)** - An open-world RPG celebrated for its rich narrative, deep characters, and vast world to explore.\n\n3. **Doom (1993)** - A seminal first-person shooter that set the standard for the genre and popularized 3D graphics in gaming.\n\n4. **World of Warcraft (2004)** - A massively multiplayer online role-playing game (MMORPG) that became a cultural phenomenon and defined the genre for years.\n\n5. **Minecraft (2011)** - A sandbox game that allows players to build and explore virtual worlds made of blocks, fostering creativity and entertainment.\n\n6. **Counter-Strike: Global Offensive (2012)** - A competitive first-person shooter that has maintained a strong esports presence and player base.\n\n7. **Starcraft II (2010)** - A highly regarded real-time strategy game known for its competitive gameplay and rich lore in the Starcraft universe.\n\n8. **The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim (2011)** - An open-world RPG known for its expansive world, modding community, and engaging questlines.\n\n9. **Civilization V (2010)** - A turn-based strategy game that invites players to build and expand their civilization through the ages.\n\n10. **Portal 2 (2011)** - A unique puzzle-platformer mixing puzzle-solving with a witty narrative and inventive gameplay mechanics.\n\nWhile these games are significant in the history of PC gaming, personal preferences will vary, and new contenders are always emerging.",
